# Rule: English (`/en/`) pages – internal link localization

## Goal

Every file inside `src/app/en/` must use English-prefixed navigation. Plain `Link` from `next/link` and bare `<a href>` tags that point to internal paths must be replaced with the project's dedicated helpers.

## Helpers available in this project

| Helper | Import path | When to use |
|--------|-------------|-------------|
| `EnLink` | `@/app/en/_components/EnLink` | Drop-in replacement for `<Link href="...">` |
| `prefixEnPath` | `@/app/en/_lib/prefixEnPath` | When you need the URL string (e.g. `router.push`, `<a href>`, `redirect()`) |

## Rules

### 1. Replace `<Link>` with `<EnLink>`

**Before:**
```tsx
import Link from "next/link"
<Link href="/about">About</Link>
```

**After:**
```tsx
import { EnLink } from "@/app/en/_components/EnLink"
<EnLink href="/about">About</EnLink>
```

> `EnLink` already adds the `/en` prefix internally – do NOT pass `/en/about`.

### 2. Replace bare `<a href="...">` with `<EnLink>` (internal paths only)

**Before:**
```html
<a href="/contact">Contact</a>
```

**After:**
```tsx
<EnLink href="/contact">Contact</EnLink>
```

> Only for **internal** paths (starting with `/`). Leave external URLs (`https://...`) as `<a>`.

### 3. Use `prefixEnPath()` for programmatic navigation

**Before:**
```ts
router.push("/dashboard")
redirect("/login")
```

**After:**
```ts
import { prefixEnPath } from "@/app/en/_lib/prefixEnPath"
router.push(prefixEnPath("/dashboard"))
redirect(prefixEnPath("/login"))
```

## What NOT to change

- External links (`href="https://..."`, `href="mailto:..."`, `href="tel:..."`)
- Anchor links (`href="#section"`)
- The `EnLink` / `prefixEnPath` definitions themselves
- Files **outside** the `src/app/en/` directory

## Shared components with locale prop

When using `SiteHeader`, `SiteFooter`, `CookieBanner`, or `BlogShell` inside `/en` pages, always pass `locale="en"` so they render English-prefixed links:

```tsx
<SiteHeader locale="en" />
<SiteFooter locale="en" />
<CookieBanner locale="en" />
<BlogShell locale="en">...</BlogShell>
```

## Checklist when editing a file in `src/app/en/`

1. [ ] No bare `import Link from "next/link"` for internal nav (use `<EnLink>` instead)
2. [ ] No `<Link href="/...">` pointing to internal paths without `/en` prefix
3. [ ] No `<a href="/...">` for internal navigation
4. [ ] All `router.push` / `redirect` / `useRouter` calls use `prefixEnPath()`
5. [ ] `SiteHeader`, `SiteFooter`, `CookieBanner`, `BlogShell` receive `locale="en"` when used in `/en`
